  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(3) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Shining.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—Better, perhaps, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "glittering.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Exceeding white as snow.—The two last words are wanting in the best MSS. The comparison of the bright raiment with clothes that had just passed through the fuller’s or bleacher’s hands, is, in its homely vividness, peculiar to St. Mark.",
