  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And his raiment became shining,.... With the rays of glory and brightness which darted from his body through his clothes, and made them as bright as the light of the sun at noon day: and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "exceeding white as snow; than which nothing is whiter; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "so as no fuller on earth can white them. The Syriac version renders it, \"as men cannot white on earth\"; and the Persic thus, \"so as men could not behold him\". Just as the Israelites could not steadfastly behold the face of Moses, because of the glory of his countenance, when he came down from the mount; See Gill on Matthew 17:2. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "so as no fuller on earth can white them. The Syriac version renders it, \"as men cannot white on earth\"; and the Persic thus, \"so as men could not behold him\". Just as the Israelites could not steadfastly behold the face of Moses, because of the glory of his countenance, when he came down from the mount; See Gill on ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Matthew 17:2",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". ",
            "children": []
